Description: Advanced Micro Robotics LLC is an applied robotics research company located in Dulles, Virginia about 30 miles from Washington DC.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Advanced Micro Robotics LLC is an applied robotics research company located in Dulles, Virginia  about 30 miles from Washington DC. Advanced Micro Robotics specializes in incorporating robot technologies with the latest technologies such as RFID, machine vision, and Personal Computers coupled with its own brand of easy-to-use software technology.  Advanced Micro Robotics has developed desktop/bench-top multi-axis robotic arms and XYZ linear translation stage systems capable of a variety of applications including: bottle label applications, pipetting applications and general pick and place applications. Advanced Micro Robotics has also developed a mobile robotic platform with a payload capacity of over 200 pounds and has experience with industrial robot arms. Advanced Micro Robotics can design, develop and install complete robotics systems from the ground up including custom mechanical hardware, electrical hardware and custom software. Most software is real-time system code written in C, C++ or Labview. Advanced Micro Robotics is housed in a modern 2500 square foot state-of-the-art office/lab/warehouse. Facilities include a machine shop, electronics lab, robotics lab and office space. They have extensive background in technology, is published and has been presented with many patents and awards. The owner has worked as a Vice President of Desktop Software development at AOL. During his seven year tenure at AOL he and his team designed, developed and launched AOL 3.0, 4.0, 5.0, 6.0, and 7.0 to over 30 million members in many languages worldwide on Windows, MAC and Linux platforms. Prior to AOL the owner spent several years working at Eastman Kodak’s Manufacturing, Research and Engineering Labs located in Rochester, NY. The owner was a team leader or key technical contributor for many projects including AI based machine vision systems, high speed LED printers, and high speed CO2 laser printers.  As a small company with fully stocked lab resources they can move quickly in an inexpensive fashion to provide you with robotics solutions that will meet your needs. Give us a call today. They will be more than happy to discuss the possibilities with you.
Industry Groups: Hardware, Manufacturing, Science and Engineering, Software

Description: Oomf is a software platform enabling the sharing economy.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Oomf is a cloud-software platform that enables the sharing economy – one thing at a time. They partner with manufacturers so that they can integrate their products into our platform to make them shareable.  Then, they distribute their products to markets where sharing makes sense.  Finally, they find sponsors who subsidize the cost of the shareable device so that its low- or no-cost for for the consumer to temporarily use.   The first product integrations into the Oomf platform are two portable chargers: one for a smartphone and another for a laptop.  Using the Oomf app, Oomf users can locate a portable charger, use it temporarily and return it when fully-charged.  Currently, we’re offering our shareable power service on collegiate campuses, but we’re planning to expand into other market verticals toward the end of 2017.  At the same time, we’ll begin to explore new shareable product integrations.  In 10 years, any “thing” that can be shareable, will be shareable on the Oomf platform.
